386→                        <div id="content">If $z_1,\ldots,z_n\in \mathbb{C}$ with $\lvert z_i\rvert=1$ then is it true that the probability that\[\lvert \epsilon_1z_1+\cdots+\epsilon_nz_n\rvert \leq \sqrt{2},\]where $\epsilon_i\in \{-1,1\}$ uniformly at random, is $\gg 1/n$?</div>
387→                        <div id="problem_id"><a href="/395">#395</a>: <a href="#cite-Er45-395" onclick="event.preventDefault();addNewBox('Er45','395'); return false;">[Er45]</a></div>
